THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 234 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. The State of Nevada exempts itself from the provisions of
4 15 U.S.C. § 260a(a) requiring the advancement of time during the
5 period commencing at 2 a.m. on the second Sunday of March of
6 each year and ending at 2 a.m. on the first Sunday of November of
7 each year, commonly known as daylight saving time.
8 2. During the period described in subsection 1, the State of
9 Nevada and all political subdivisions thereof shall observe the
10 standard time otherwise applicable for the time zone in which the
11 State is situated in accordance with the provisions of 15 U.S.C. §§
12 260 et seq., the solar time of the 120th meridian west of
13 Greenwich, commonly known as Pacific Standard Time.
14 Sec. 2. This act becomes effective on January 1, 2026.
